Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil on high heat. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Add them to the water with @salt{0.25%tsp}. Bring back to the boil. Once boiling reduce the heat slightly and cook until the potatoes are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

When cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Preheat your #oven{} to 200 °C.

Meanwhile, put the @dried Italian herbs{1%tsp}, @panko breadcrumbs{12.5%g} and @water{1%tbsp} per person into a large #mixing bowl{}. Mix together, then add the @British pork mince{120%g} and @British beef mince{120%g}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Use your hands to mix the seasonings into the meat then shape into small balls (5 per person).

> TIP: Make sure you roll them well in the palms of your hands to prevent them falling apart when cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Heat a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the meatballs and cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}, turning occasionally.

> TIP: Do this in batches if necessary, you want the meatballs to brown not stew!

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. When the meatballs are browned, transfer to a #plate{} then drain any remaining fat out of the pan. Add the onion and @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} to the pan. Cook until the onion is soft, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the meatballs back into the pan.

Add the @water for the sauce{125%ml} and the @chicken stock powder{1%tsp} to the meatballs. Stir then lower the heat. Cover the pan with a #lid{} or foil and simmer until the meatballs are cooked through, ~{7-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve any large @broccoli florets{200%g} and pop them on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{1%splash} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Roast in the oven until browned and tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Mash the potatoes with a #potato masher{} then stir in the grated cheddar. Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Keep warm with the lid on while you finish off.

> TIP: Add a splash of milk and a knob of butter if you have it.

When the meatballs are cooked through, remove the lid and stir in the @redcurrant jelly{25%g}. Increase the heat and bubble the sauce until it is glossy and has thickened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}. Share the mash between your plates and serve the broccoli florets alongside. Pop the meatballs on top of the mash and finish with a generous helping of gravy. Enjoy!